# =============================================================================
# .gitignore
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Keep the repo light: gathered datasets, model weights, secrets, and the usual
# Python/editor cruft stay out of version control. Folder structure under data/
# is preserved via .gitkeep files; the large payloads inside are ignored.
# =============================================================================

# --- Secrets ---
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.setup_state.json

# --- Claude Code agent tooling (not part of the project) ---
.agents/
skills-lock.json

# --- Internal build/planning docs (kept locally, not in the public repo) ---
/CLAUDE.md
/kickoff.md
/prep/
/docs/build_plan.md
/docs/integration-kickoff.md
/docs/showcase-kickoff.md
/docs/tech_and_sponsors.md
/docs/SAR_project_plan.md
/docs/brain_followups.md
/docs/demo_scenario.md
/docs/geo_detector_integration.md

# --- Gathered data (large; tracked by structure only, not contents) ---
data/terrain/*
data/detection/*
data/footage/*
data/behavior/*
data/weights/*
# ...but keep the empty-folder markers and any small docs we choose to commit
!data/**/.gitkeep
!data/README.md
!data/**/*.md

# --- Model weights anywhere else ---
*.pt
*.pth
*.onnx
*.tflite
*.engine

# --- Python ---
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/
.venv/
venv/
.ipynb_checkpoints/
.pytest_cache/
.coverage
htmlcov/

# --- Node / frontend (covers any node project in the repo, not just dashboard_app/) ---
node_modules/
dist/
dist-ssr/
.vite/
*.tsbuildinfo
*.local

# --- Demo render output (regenerated by src/demo/run.py) ---
demo_output/

# --- OS / editor ---
.DS_Store
.vscode/
.idea/
